      "content": "Originalism proponents argue that the Constitution should be interpreted based on its original meaning at the time it was ratified. They contend that the Founders intended the document to have specific meanings, and judges should adhere to those historical understandings. This perspective emphasizes that the Constitution is a fixed text, not a malleable document subject to modern societal shifts. Therefore, originalists believe that judicial interpretation should aim for fidelity to the historical text and intent.",
