    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. So it kind of comes down to how you view the role of a judge. Some say the whole thing is just an outdated way of thinking that doesn't work for a modern democracy, while others see it as essential for stability. If you had to categorize it, would you say originalism is a mainstream, respected legal theory, or is it more of an ideological tool used primarily by certain political factions?",
