      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism is certainly a highly influential and deeply respected theory within certain legal and academic circles, forming a major point of contention in modern jurisprudence. However, it is also widely criticized by those who advocate for more living constitutionalist approaches. Therefore, it functions as both a legitimate, sophisticated legal methodology and a potent ideological tool used by various political factions seeking specific policy outcomes. It is best understood as a central, highly debated framework in contemporary constitutional theory.",
      "source": "target",
